---
import Layout from "@/layouts/Layout.astro";
import SiteHeader from "@/components/SiteHeader.astro";
import SiteFooter from "@/components/SiteFooter.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="LetsChat Self-Hosting Guide"
  description="Step-by-step production guide for self-hosting LetsChat backend with Cloudflare Tunnel or Caddy reverse proxy."
>
  <SiteHeader active="self-hosting" />

  <main class="relative max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 py-16 space-y-14 overflow-hidden">
    <div class="hero-glow hero-glow-a"></div>
    <div class="hero-glow hero-glow-b"></div>

    <section class="relative z-10 grid lg:grid-cols-[1.1fr_0.9fr] gap-6 items-start">
      <div class="space-y-4">
        <p class="inline-flex text-xs px-3 py-1 rounded-full border border-border text-muted-foreground">Beginner-first production tutorial (Ubuntu + Docker Compose)</p>
        <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-semibold tracking-tight">Self-host the LetsChat backend</h1>
        <p class="guide-prose max-w-3xl">
          LetsChat is not a single server. It is a small backend stack: chat state, auth, voice signaling, file storage,
          and startup discovery. This guide explains what each part does, why it matters, and then walks you through one
          of two deployment paths.
        </p>
        <p class="guide-prose max-w-3xl">
          The same stack serves <strong>both ways to connect</strong>: the installable <strong>desktop app</strong> and a
          hosted <strong>browser client</strong> at <code class="text-xs">app.&lt;domain&gt;</code> — no install required, voice included.
        </p>
        <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 text-xs">
          <span class="pill">SpacetimeDB</span>
          <span class="pill">Auth Service</span>
          <span class="pill">LiveKit</span>
          <span class="pill">MinIO</span>
          <span class="pill">Browser Client</span>
          <span class="pill">Discovery URL</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <aside class="frost p-5 rounded-2xl space-y-4">
        <p class="text-sm font-medium text-foreground">Architecture At A Glance</p>
        <div class="space-y-2 text-sm">
          <div class="flow-chip"><span>Desktop or Browser</span><span class="flow-dot"></span><span>auth.example.com</span></div>
          <div class="flow-chip"><span>Discovery JSON</span><span class="flow-dot"></span><span>auth/chat/lk/files URLs</span></div>
          <div class="flow-chip"><span>Runtime Services</span><span class="flow-dot"></span><span>Auth + Spacetime + LiveKit + MinIO + Web</span></div>
        </div>
        <p class="text-xs text-muted-foreground"><code class="text-xs">auth.&lt;domain&gt;</code> doubles as the discovery entrypoint — startup auto-configures backend endpoints with no manual join links.</p>
      </aside>
    </section>

    <section class="frost rounded-2xl p-6 space-y-4">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight">What Runs In Production (And Why)</h2>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-4 text-sm">
        <article class="service-card rounded-xl p-4 space-y-1">
          <p class="font-medium">SpacetimeDB</p>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground">Real-time chat/game state backend. Required for channels, messages, membership, and sync.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="service-card rounded-xl p-4 space-y-1">
          <p class="font-medium">Auth Service</p>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground">Login/session API and token minting. Required for user authentication and LiveKit token creation.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="service-card rounded-xl p-4 space-y-1">
          <p class="font-medium">LiveKit</p>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground">Voice/media signaling and transport. Required for voice channels and real-time audio.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="service-card rounded-xl p-4 space-y-1">
          <p class="font-medium">MinIO</p>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground">S3-compatible object storage. Required for uploads, attachments, and download URLs.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="service-card rounded-xl p-4 space-y-1">
          <p class="font-medium">Module Init</p>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground">One-shot container that publishes the SpacetimeDB WASM module on startup. Runs automatically and exits cleanly.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="service-card rounded-xl p-4 space-y-1">
          <p class="font-medium">Web Client (<code class="text-xs">app.&lt;domain&gt;</code>)</p>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground">Optional hosted browser SPA. Builds the React bundle pinned to this instance, so users can run LetsChat in a browser — voice included — without installing the desktop app.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="service-card rounded-xl p-4 space-y-1 md:col-span-2 lg:col-span-1">
          <p class="font-medium">Discovery Endpoint (<code class="text-xs">/.well-known/letschat.json</code>)</p>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground">Served by core-api on <code class="text-xs">auth.&lt;domain&gt;</code>, so app startup auto-discovers your backend from one URL (for example <code class="text-xs">https://auth.example.com</code>). No separate <code class="text-xs">connect</code> subdomain. Without this, users must paste a full join link manually.</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="rounded-xl border border-border bg-card/80 p-5">
      <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
        Before applying setup or upgrade steps, review
        <a href="/breaking-changes" class="text-foreground underline underline-offset-4 hover:opacity-80 transition-opacity">Breaking Changes</a>
        to avoid version mismatch and migration issues.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="space-y-4">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight">Choose Your Deployment Path</h2>
      <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground max-w-2xl">Both paths deploy the same backend stack. The difference is how HTTPS traffic reaches your server.</p>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <a href="/self-hosting/cloudflare-tunnel" class="track-card tunnel rounded-xl p-5 space-y-2">
          <p class="text-lg font-medium">Path A: Cloudflare Tunnel</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground"><strong class="text-foreground">What:</strong> Routes <code class="text-xs">auth/chat/files/app</code> and LiveKit signalling over Cloudflare Tunnel; only LiveKit media stays direct via forwarded ports.</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground"><strong class="text-foreground">Why:</strong> Keeps web services off direct public IP while still supporting voice traffic.</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground"><strong class="text-foreground">Best for:</strong> Home servers where you want Cloudflare ingress control without exposing 80/443 directly.</p>
          <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 pt-1">
            <span class="mini-pill">Zero Trust Ingress</span>
            <span class="mini-pill">Lower Host Exposure</span>
          </div>
          <p class="text-xs text-accent-blue font-medium pt-1">Read the guide →</p>
        </a>
        <a href="/self-hosting/caddy" class="track-card caddy rounded-xl p-5 space-y-2">
          <p class="text-lg font-medium">Path B: Caddy Reverse Proxy</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground"><strong class="text-foreground">What:</strong> Caddy terminates TLS on your host and proxies <code class="text-xs">auth/chat/files/lk/app</code> locally.</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground"><strong class="text-foreground">Why:</strong> Simple standard architecture with fewer external moving parts.</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground"><strong class="text-foreground">Best for:</strong> Operators comfortable exposing 80/443 and managing direct DNS to host IP.</p>
          <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 pt-1">
            <span class="mini-pill">Direct HTTPS</span>
            <span class="mini-pill">Classic Reverse Proxy</span>
          </div>
          <p class="text-xs text-accent-blue font-medium pt-1">Read the guide →</p>
        </a>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="space-y-4">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight">Common Mistakes</h2>
      <div class="overflow-x-auto rounded-2xl border border-border/70 bg-card/60 backdrop-blur-sm">
        <table class="w-full text-sm">
          <thead class="bg-card text-left">
            <tr>
              <th class="p-3 font-medium">Problem</th>
              <th class="p-3 font-medium">Likely cause</th>
              <th class="p-3 font-medium">Fix</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody class="divide-y divide-border text-muted-foreground">
            <tr>
              <td class="p-3">Voice joins but no audio</td>
              <td class="p-3">LiveKit media ports not forwarded</td>
              <td class="p-3">Forward <code class="text-xs">44382/udp</code> (primary) and <code class="text-xs">44381/tcp</code> (fallback) to host</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="p-3">Setup discovery fails</td>
              <td class="p-3"><code class="text-xs">auth.&lt;domain&gt;</code> not serving <code class="text-xs">/.well-known/letschat.json</code></td>
              <td class="p-3">Tunnel: <code class="text-xs">auth → core-api:8787</code>; Caddy: set <code class="text-xs">AUTH_DOMAIN</code> + DNS</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="p-3">Browser client can't download files</td>
              <td class="p-3"><code class="text-xs">MINIO_CORS_ALLOW_ORIGIN</code> doesn't match the web origin</td>
              <td class="p-3">Set it to <code class="text-xs">https://app.&lt;domain&gt;</code> (or <code class="text-xs">*</code>)</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="p-3">Upload/download errors</td>
              <td class="p-3">Wrong <code class="text-xs">MINIO_PUBLIC_ENDPOINT</code></td>
              <td class="p-3">Set to public <code class="text-xs">https://files...</code> endpoint clients can reach</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="p-3">Caddy cert issuance fails</td>
              <td class="p-3">Cloudflare proxy enabled or closed 80/443</td>
              <td class="p-3">Use DNS-only records and open <code class="text-xs">80/tcp</code>, <code class="text-xs">443/tcp</code></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="p-3">LiveKit setup fails immediately</td>
              <td class="p-3">Wrong signalling scheme (<code class="text-xs">ws://</code> vs <code class="text-xs">wss://</code>)</td>
              <td class="p-3">Both tracks use <code class="text-xs">wss://lk...</code> — signalling is TLS-terminated (Cloudflare tunnel ingress or Caddy). Plain <code class="text-xs">ws://</code> is dev-only</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="p-3">Spacetime connect timeout</td>
              <td class="p-3"><code class="text-xs">module-init</code> failed or SpacetimeDB not yet healthy</td>
              <td class="p-3">Check <code class="text-xs">docker logs letschat-module-init</code>; it retries on failure automatically</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
  <SiteFooter />
</Layout>

<style>
  .hero-glow {
    position: absolute;
    pointer-events: none;
    border-radius: 9999px;
    filter: blur(56px);
    opacity: 0.22;
  }

  .hero-glow-a {
    width: 360px;
    height: 260px;
    top: -80px;
    left: -80px;
    background: radial-gradient(circle at 40% 40%, color-mix(in oklch, var(--accent-blue) 80%, white 20%), transparent 70%);
    animation: drift 12s ease-in-out infinite;
  }

  .hero-glow-b {
    width: 340px;
    height: 240px;
    top: 120px;
    right: -120px;
    background: radial-gradient(circle at 60% 50%, color-mix(in oklch, var(--accent-blue) 70%, cyan 30%), transparent 72%);
    animation: drift 15s ease-in-out infinite reverse;
  }

  .frost {
    background:
      linear-gradient(160deg, oklch(0.24 0 0 / 0.8), oklch(0.20 0 0 / 0.75)),
      radial-gradient(1200px 380px at -10% -30%, oklch(0.54 0.23 264.3 / 0.16), transparent 60%);
    border: 1px solid oklch(1 0 0 / 0.11);
    box-shadow:
      0 1px 0 oklch(1 0 0 / 0.08) inset,
      0 20px 50px oklch(0 0 0 / 0.24);
    backdrop-filter: blur(8px);
  }

  .pill {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    padding: 0.35rem 0.65rem;
    border-radius: 9999px;
    border: 1px solid oklch(1 0 0 / 0.16);
    background: oklch(0.23 0 0 / 0.72);
    color: var(--color-muted-foreground);
  }

  .flow-chip {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr auto 1fr;
    gap: 0.55rem;
    align-items: center;
    padding: 0.58rem 0.72rem;
    border-radius: 0.72rem;
    border: 1px solid oklch(1 0 0 / 0.1);
    background: oklch(0.18 0 0 / 0.64);
    color: var(--color-muted-foreground);
  }

  .flow-dot {
    width: 0.42rem;
    height: 0.42rem;
    border-radius: 9999px;
    background: var(--color-accent-blue);
    box-shadow: 0 0 0 6px oklch(0.49 0.23 264.3 / 0.18);
  }

  .service-card {
    border: 1px solid oklch(1 0 0 / 0.12);
    background: linear-gradient(180deg, oklch(0.21 0 0 / 0.88), oklch(0.19 0 0 / 0.88));
    box-shadow: 0 12px 28px oklch(0 0 0 / 0.2);
  }

  .track-card {
    position: relative;
    border: 1px solid oklch(1 0 0 / 0.14);
    background: linear-gradient(180deg, oklch(0.22 0 0 / 0.9), oklch(0.18 0 0 / 0.86));
    box-shadow: 0 14px 32px oklch(0 0 0 / 0.2);
    overflow: hidden;
    transition: transform 220ms ease, border-color 220ms ease, box-shadow 220ms ease;
    display: block;
  }

  .track-card::before {
    content: "";
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0 0 auto 0;
    height: 3px;
    background: linear-gradient(90deg, transparent, var(--color-accent-blue), transparent);
    opacity: 0.75;
  }

  .track-card:hover {
    transform: translateY(-2px);
    border-color: oklch(1 0 0 / 0.24);
    box-shadow: 0 20px 40px oklch(0 0 0 / 0.28);
  }

  .track-card.tunnel {
    background:
      linear-gradient(165deg, oklch(0.23 0.02 260 / 0.96), oklch(0.18 0 0 / 0.9)),
      radial-gradient(420px 180px at 120% -10%, oklch(0.49 0.23 264.3 / 0.25), transparent 65%);
  }

  .track-card.caddy {
    background:
      linear-gradient(165deg, oklch(0.22 0.01 220 / 0.96), oklch(0.18 0 0 / 0.9)),
      radial-gradient(420px 180px at 120% -10%, oklch(0.74 0.16 190 / 0.2), transparent 65%);
  }

  .mini-pill {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    border-radius: 9999px;
    padding: 0.28rem 0.55rem;
    border: 1px solid oklch(1 0 0 / 0.16);
    font-size: 0.68rem;
    color: var(--color-muted-foreground);
    background: oklch(0.16 0 0 / 0.6);
  }

  @keyframes drift {
    0% { transform: translate3d(0, 0, 0) scale(1); }
    50% { transform: translate3d(8px, -12px, 0) scale(1.04); }
    100% { transform: translate3d(0, 0, 0) scale(1); }
  }
</style>

